# 3. Streaming Data Generation

To simulate real-world ecommerce traffic, the platform generates synthetic clickstream events representing user interactions.

Example event types include:

- product view
- add to cart
- purchase
- session start

Each event contains metadata such as:

| Field | Description |
|------|-------------|
| user_id | unique customer identifier |
| session_id | browsing session identifier |
| product_id | product interacted with |
| event_type | user action |
| price | product price |
| timestamp | event time |

Events are written as small batch files and streamed into the pipeline to emulate real-time traffic.

