# 7. Label Generation

Supervised learning models require labeled datasets.

Labels are derived from behavioral signals.

Example labels:

| Label | Description |
|------|-------------|
| label_purchase | whether a purchase occurred |
| label_fraud | potential suspicious activity |

These labels allow the training of:

- purchase prediction models
- fraud detection models

---

# 8. Data Storage Format

All tables are stored using **Delta Lake**.

Delta Lake provides several advantages:

- ACID transactions
- schema enforcement
- time travel
- efficient storage

These features improve data reliability and operational stability.

---

# 9. Pipeline Reliability

Several practices ensure pipeline reliability:

- immutable Bronze data
- deterministic feature transformations
- Delta Lake transactional storage
- modular notebook pipelines

These practices enable reproducible and maintainable data pipelines.

